  "prompt": "Why won't my iPod touch turn on?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why your iPod touch won't turn on:\n\n1. Battery is completely drained\n- Charge it using the original charger for at least 30 minutes\n- Try a different charging cable or power adapter\n\n2. Software issue\n- Force restart by pressing and holding the home button and power button simultaneously for 10-15 seconds\n- If no home button, press and quickly release volume up, volume down, then press and hold the power button\n\n3. Hardware problems\n- Damaged charging port\n- Faulty battery\n- Internal component failure\n\n4. Physical damage\n- Water damage\n- Significant impact or drop\n\nRecommended troubleshooting steps:\n- Ensure charger and cable are working\n- Try different power sources\n- Perform a force restart\n- Check for visible physical damage\n\nIf these steps don't work, you may need to:\n- Contact Apple Support\n- Visit an Apple Store or authorized service provider\n- Consider professional repair or replacement",
